medical_history.chief_complaint: Tachypnea and dysphoria five hours after birth.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began five hours after birth and included tachypnea, dysphoria, convulsions, and irritability. Metabolic acidosis was initially corrected but reappeared once no alkaline liquid was added. Blood lactate levels remained consistently elevated during the 13-day hospital stay, with post-discharge follow-up noting ongoing issues.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Increased biparietal diameter and head circumference during pregnancy, presence of subependymal cysts, and a microdeletion on chromosome 10 detected during amniocentesis. No other past medical conditions were specified.
